oc:kn_036008fc a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When loading playbook in Step 3" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If no playbook is configured, explicitly inform the user and clearly note the review is based on general commercial standards, not organization-specific positions." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Generic standards may not reflect the organization's risk tolerance or deal posture" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_0a7ed531 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When flagging deviations in Step 5" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Classify deviations using three tiers: GREEN (acceptable, note only), YELLOW (negotiate, generate redlines with fallback), RED (escalate, estimate exposure). Use the negotiation priority framework: Tier 1 must-haves, Tier 2 should-haves, Tier 3 nice-to-haves." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Structured triage prevents over-negotiating minor points and under-escalating material risks" .

oc:kn_3b63b734 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When performing clause-by-clause analysis" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Read the entire contract before flagging issues — clauses interact with each other (e.g., an uncapped indemnity may be partially mitigated by a broad limitation of liability)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Isolated clause review can produce misleading severity assessments when provisions offset each other" .

oc:kn_3f1842e0 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating redline suggestions" ;
    oc:directiveContent "For redline generation: be specific (exact language), balanced (commercially reasonable), and always provide fallback positions. Adjust tone based on relationship type (new vendor vs. strategic partner vs. commodity supplier)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Overly aggressive redlines slow negotiations; vague redlines are unusable" .

oc:kn_72510096 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When accepting very long or non-English contracts" ;
    oc:directiveContent "For contracts 50+ pages, offer to focus on the most material sections first, then do a complete review. For non-English contracts, ask if translation or original-language review is preferred." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Lengthy contracts can exceed processing capacity; language differences can cause nuance loss" .

oc:kn_931258de a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "always" ;
    oc:directiveContent "This skill assists with legal workflows but does NOT provide legal advice. All analysis must be reviewed by qualified legal professionals before being relied upon." ;
    oc:hasRationale "AI-generated legal analysis carries liability risk and must be validated by licensed counsel" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_959d89eb a oc:AssumptionBoundary,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When gathering context in Step 2" ;
    oc:directiveContent "The user's side (vendor/customer/licensor/licensee/partner) fundamentally changes which clause positions are favorable. Always confirm side before analyzing." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The same limitation of liability clause may be favorable or unfavorable depending on which party the user represents" .

